cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AI 

This paper deals with the security analysis of cyber-physical systems, which are typically modeled using control theory and signal processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems. The paper also discusses security properties, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper proposes a new simulation relation, which could be of interest to researchers in cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper discusses the construction of symbolic models, which could be relevant to researchers in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
